{
  "openapi": "3.0.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "FDO Owner Server API (Deprecated)",
    "version": "1.1.0",
    "description": "API for the FDO Owner Server role. The Owner Server is responsible for managing\ndevice ownership, including ownership vouchers, trusted device CA certificates,\nand rendezvous TO2 addresses for device onboarding.\n\nThis specification aggregates the following management APIs:\n- Ownership Voucher Management (/api/v1/vouchers)\n- Trusted Device CA Certificates (/api/v1/device-ca)\n- RVTO2 Address Configuration (/api/v1/rvto2addr)\n\n## API Versioning\nThis API uses semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) and includes the major\nversion in the URL path (e.g., `/api/v1/vouchers`).\n\n- **MAJOR version** changes indicate breaking changes (incompatible API changes)\n- **MINOR version** changes add functionality in a backward-compatible manner\n- **PATCH version** changes are backward-compatible bug fixes\n\n### Version Support Policy\n- The current major version (v1) is fully supported\n- When a new major version is released, the previous major version will be\n  supported for a minimum of 12 months\n- Deprecated endpoints or fields will be marked in the documentation and\n  supported for at least 6 months before removal\n- Deprecation notices will include the deprecation date, removal date, and\n  migration guidance\n\n### Breaking Changes\nBreaking changes that trigger a major version increment include:\n- Removing or renaming endpoints\n- Removing or renaming request/response fields\n- Changing field types or validation rules\n- Changing authentication mechanisms\n\n## Pagination\nList operations support pagination using `offset` and `limit` query parameters:\n- `offset`: Number of items to skip (default: 0, minimum: 0)\n- `limit`: Maximum number of items to return (default: 100, minimum: 1, maximum: 1000)\n\n## Rate Limiting\nAPI requests may be subject to rate limiting to ensure service stability.\nRate limit information is provided in response headers when applicable:\n- `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Maximum requests allowed in the time window\n- `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Remaining requests in the current window\n- `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Time when the rate limit resets (Unix timestamp)\n\nWhen rate limits are exceeded, the API returns a 429 Too Many Requests status code.\n\n## Request Body Size Limit\nAll management API endpoints enforce a maximum request body size of 10MB.\nRequests exceeding this limit will receive a `413 Payload Too Large` response.\n",
    "contact": {
      "name": "Go FDO Server API Support",
      "url": "https://github.com/fido-device-onboard/go-fdo-server/issues"
    }
  },
  "paths": {
    "/health": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GetHealth",
        "summary": "Get server health status",
        "description": "Returns the server version and health status.\n\nNote: This endpoint does not require authentication and is intended\nfor health checks by monitoring systems and load balancers.\n",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/HealthStatus"
          },
          "500": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/InternalServerError",
            "examples": {
              "error": {
                "summary": "Example of an unhealthy server",
                "value": {
                  "message": "database error"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "health"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/api/v1/owner/vouchers": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "ListVouchers",
        "summary": "Query ownership vouchers (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Returns a list of ownership vouchers matching optional filter criteria.\n\nResults are ordered by updated_at timestamp in descending order.\nThe CBOR field is omitted from results (use GET /vouchers/{guid} to retrieve full voucher).\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "guid",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filter by device GUID (hex-encoded)",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "example": "3f4e5d6c7b8a9f0e1d2c3b4a5f6e7d8c",
              "pattern": "^[0-9a-fA-F]{32}$"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "device_info",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filter by device info string",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "example": "MyDevice"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successfully retrieved voucher list",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": {
                    "$ref": "#/components/schemas/VoucherMetadata"
                  }
                },
                "examples": {
                  "emptyList": {
                    "summary": "No vouchers found",
                    "value": []
                  },
                  "voucherList": {
                    "summary": "List of vouchers",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "guid": "3f4e5d6c7b8a9f0e1d2c3b4a5f6e7d8c",
                        "device_info": "Device 1",
                        "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
                        "updated_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
                      },
                      {
                        "guid": "a1b2c3d4e5f6789012345678abcdef01",
                        "device_info": "Device 2",
                        "created_at": "2024-01-14T09:20:00Z",
                        "updated_at": "2024-01-14T09:20:00Z"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid query parameters",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "Invalid GUID: xyz"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred while querying vouchers",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "vouchers"
        ]
      },
      "post": {
        "operationId": "InsertVoucher",
        "summary": "Insert ownership voucher(s) (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Inserts one or more ownership vouchers into the database.\n\nThe request body should contain PEM-encoded ownership voucher(s).\nEach voucher is verified for:\n- Ownership (voucher owner key matches server's configured keys)\n- Cryptographic integrity (signature chain, certificate chains, etc.)\n- Protocol version and header field validity\n\nDuplicate vouchers (same GUID with same CBOR data) are silently skipped.\nExisting vouchers (same GUID with different CBOR data) are not overwritten and are silently skipped.\n\nThe operation succeeds (200 OK) even if all vouchers were duplicates/skipped.\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "PEM-encoded ownership voucher(s)",
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/x-pem-file": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "binary"
              },
              "example": "-----BEGIN OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n[base64-encoded CBOR data]\n-----END OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n"
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Voucher(s) successfully inserted or were duplicates",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "example": ""
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid voucher data or verification failed",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "decodeCborError": {
                    "summary": "Unable to decode CBOR",
                    "value": "Unable to decode cbor"
                  },
                  "invalidVoucher": {
                    "summary": "Voucher verification failed",
                    "value": "Invalid ownership voucher"
                  },
                  "decodePemError": {
                    "summary": "Unable to decode PEM",
                    "value": "Unable to decode PEM content"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "413": {
            "description": "Request payload too large (exceeds maximum allowed size).",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "http: request body too large"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred while inserting voucher",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "readBodyError": {
                    "summary": "Error reading request body",
                    "value": "Failure to read the request body"
                  },
                  "insertError": {
                    "summary": "Error inserting into database",
                    "value": "Internal server error"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "vouchers"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/api/v1/owner/vouchers/{guid}": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GetVoucherByGUID",
        "summary": "Get ownership voucher by GUID (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Retrieves a specific ownership voucher by its device GUID.\n\nReturns the voucher in PEM format with full CBOR data.\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "guid",
            "in": "path",
            "description": "Device GUID (hex-encoded, 32 characters)",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "example": "3f4e5d6c7b8a9f0e1d2c3b4a5f6e7d8c",
              "pattern": "^[0-9a-fA-F]{32}$"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successfully retrieved the ownership voucher",
            "content": {
              "application/x-pem-file": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "binary"
                },
                "example": "-----BEGIN OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n[base64-encoded CBOR data]\n-----END OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n"
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid GUID format",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "invalidGuid": {
                    "summary": "Invalid GUID",
                    "value": "Invalid GUID"
                  },
                  "invalidFormat": {
                    "summary": "Invalid GUID format",
                    "value": "Invalid GUID format"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Voucher not found",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "Voucher not found"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "vouchers"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/api/v1/owner/resell/{guid}": {
      "post": {
        "operationId": "ResellVoucher",
        "summary": "Resell ownership voucher to new owner (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Extends an ownership voucher to a new owner by adding a new entry to the signature chain.\n\nThis operation:\n1. Retrieves the current voucher by GUID\n2. Extends it with the new owner's public key\n3. Deletes the old voucher\n4. Inserts the extended voucher\n5. Returns the extended voucher in PEM format\n\nThe operation is atomic (wrapped in a database transaction).\nIf any step fails, the transaction is rolled back and the original voucher is preserved.\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "guid",
            "in": "path",
            "description": "Device GUID (hex-encoded, 32 characters)",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "example": "3f4e5d6c7b8a9f0e1d2c3b4a5f6e7d8c",
              "pattern": "^[0-9a-fA-F]{32}$"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "PEM-encoded public key of the new owner",
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/x-pem-file": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "string",
                "format": "binary"
              },
              "example": "-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n[base64-encoded public key]\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n"
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successfully resold voucher to new owner",
            "content": {
              "application/x-pem-file": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "binary"
                },
                "example": "-----BEGIN OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n[base64-encoded extended CBOR data]\n-----END OWNERSHIP VOUCHER-----\n"
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid GUID, request body, or unsupported key type",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "invalidGuid": {
                    "summary": "Invalid GUID",
                    "value": "GUID is not a valid GUID"
                  },
                  "invalidFormat": {
                    "summary": "Invalid GUID format",
                    "value": "Invalid GUID format"
                  },
                  "unsupportedKeyType": {
                    "summary": "Unsupported public key type",
                    "value": "Unsupported public key type"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Voucher not found for the specified GUID",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "Voucher not found for the specified GUID"
              }
            }
          },
          "413": {
            "description": "Request payload too large (exceeds maximum allowed size).",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "http: request body too large"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred during resell operation",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "readBodyError": {
                    "summary": "Error reading request body",
                    "value": "Failure to read the request body"
                  },
                  "invalidPem": {
                    "summary": "Invalid PEM content",
                    "value": "Invalid PEM content"
                  },
                  "parseKeyError": {
                    "summary": "Error parsing public key",
                    "value": "Error parsing x.509 public key"
                  },
                  "resellError": {
                    "summary": "Error reselling voucher",
                    "value": "Error reselling voucher"
                  },
                  "marshalError": {
                    "summary": "Error marshaling voucher",
                    "value": "Error marshaling voucher"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "resell"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/api/v1/owner/redirect": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "GetRVTO2Addr",
        "summary": "Get the current owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Retrieves the current rendezvous TO2 (Transfer of Ownership 2) address\nconfiguration that specifies where devices should connect to the owner server\nafter completing the rendezvous protocol.\n\n(Deprecated: please use \"/rvto2addr\" endpoint instead)\n",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successfully retrieved the owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RVTO2Addr"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "simpleHttpConfig": {
                    "summary": "Simple HTTP configuration with DNS",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "http",
                        "dns": "owner.example.com",
                        "port": "8080"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "httpsWithDNS": {
                    "summary": "HTTPS configuration with DNS",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-secure.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "httpsWithIP": {
                    "summary": "HTTPS configuration with IP address",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "ip": "192.168.1.100",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "httpsWithBothDnsAndIP": {
                    "summary": "HTTPS configuration with both DNS and IP",
                    "description": "Both dns and ip can be provided together",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner.example.com",
                        "ip": "192.168.1.100",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "multipleAddresses": {
                    "summary": "Multiple addresses with primary and backup",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-primary.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      },
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-backup.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      },
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "ip": "192.168.1.100",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "No RVTO2Addr configuration has been created yet.",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "No ownerInfo found"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred while fetching the configuration.",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "Error fetching ownerInfo"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "rvto2addr"
        ]
      },
      "post": {
        "operationId": "CreateRVTO2Addr",
        "summary": "Create the owner redirect info (RVTOAddr) configuration (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Creates the owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration.\n\nThe new configuration will be used by devices completing the TO2 protocol\nto determine where to connect to the owner server. This typically includes\nthe owner server's hostname/IP address, protocol, and port.\n\n(Deprecated: please use \"/rvto2addr\" endpoint instead)\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "description": "The new owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration",
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RVTO2Addr"
              },
              "examples": {
                "createHttps": {
                  "summary": "Create HTTPS with DNS",
                  "value": [
                    {
                      "protocol": "https",
                      "dns": "owner-new.example.com",
                      "port": "8443"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "createMultipleAddresses": {
                  "summary": "Create with primary and backup addresses",
                  "value": [
                    {
                      "protocol": "https",
                      "dns": "owner-primary.example.com",
                      "port": "8443"
                    },
                    {
                      "protocol": "https",
                      "dns": "owner-backup.example.com",
                      "port": "8443"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "createIPBased": {
                  "summary": "Create IP-based configuration",
                  "value": [
                    {
                      "protocol": "https",
                      "ip": "10.0.0.50",
                      "port": "8443"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "createWithBothDnsAndIP": {
                  "summary": "Create with both DNS and IP address",
                  "description": "Demonstrates that both dns and ip can be provided together",
                  "value": [
                    {
                      "protocol": "https",
                      "dns": "owner-dual.example.com",
                      "ip": "10.0.0.100",
                      "port": "8443"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "Successfully created the owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RVTO2Addr"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "createdHttpsConfiguration": {
                    "summary": "Successfully created to HTTPS configuration",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-new.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "createdMultipleAddresses": {
                    "summary": "Successfully created with multiple addresses",
                    "value": [
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-primary.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      },
                      {
                        "protocol": "https",
                        "dns": "owner-backup.example.com",
                        "port": "8443"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Invalid owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration provided in the request body.",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "Invalid ownerInfo"
              }
            }
          },
          "409": {
            "description": "Owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration already exists. Use PUT to update instead.",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "ownerInfo already exists"
              }
            }
          },
          "413": {
            "description": "Request payload too large (exceeds maximum allowed size).",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "example": "http: request body too large"
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error occurred while creating the configuration.",
            "content": {
              "text/plain": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorString"
                },
                "examples": {
                  "readError": {
                    "summary": "Error reading request body",
                    "value": "Error reading body"
                  },
                  "insertError": {
                    "summary": "Error inserting into database",
                    "value": "Error inserting ownerInfo"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "tags": [
          "rvto2addr"
        ]
      },
      "put": {
        "operationId": "UpdateRVTO2Addr",
        "summary": "Update the owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration (Deprecated)",
        "description": "Updates the owner redirect info (RVTO2Addr) configuration.\n\nThe new configuration will be used by devices completing the TO2 protocol\nto determine where to connect to the owner server. This typically includes\nthe owner server's hostname/IP address, protocol, and port.\n\n(Deprecated: please use \"/rvto2addr\" endpoint instead)\n",
